                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1014">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">du Bosc</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain at Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">Confidential.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Day</hi>: Through the minister of foreign affairs
                    in Madrid I have been instructed by Her Majesty the Queen Regent of Spain, my
                    august sovereign, to convey to the President of the United States of America her
                    expression of grief at the misfortune which has befallen the American Navy in
                    Spanish waters. Deferring entirely to your judgment in the matter, I would
                    suggest that it would be fit and proper that I should obey Her Majesty’s
                    instructions in person, and not simply <pb facs="1129" n="1033" xml:id="pg_1033"
                    /> in an official communication. If you agree with me upon this point, I beg you
                    to ask the President to grant me an audience for that express purpose. Shall be
                    glad to hear your views on the matter.</p>
                <p>Believe me, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan du Bosc</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
